 192, \"to\": 201}, {\"ngram\": \"commentary\", \"from\": 237, \"to\": 247}, {\"ngram\": \"photos\", \"from\": 252, \"to\": 258}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremonyas\", \"from\": 262, \"to\": 284}, {\"ngram\": \"the build-up\", \"from\": 293, \"to\": 305}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paris Olympics 2024 will be officially launched on Friday with an opening ceremony in the French capital that will buck the trend of all the games that have come before it.\", \"from\": 330, \"to\": 506, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 424, \"end\": 430, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.989547817742788, \"rank\": 0.010081156060865954, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 330, \"to\": 348}, {\"ngram\": \"Friday\", \"from\": 385, \"to\": 391}, {\"ngram\": \"an opening ceremony\", \"from\": 397, \"to\": 416}, {\"ngram\": \"the trend\", \"from\": 454, \"to\": 463}, {\"ngram\": \"all the games\", \"from\": 467, \"to\": 480}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Here's a breakdown of what we know ahead of what promises to be the latest in a long line of spectacularly staged curtain raisers at the Summer Olympics: For the first time in the event's history, the opening ceremony will not be staged inside an Olympic stadium.\", \"from\": 508, \"to\": 772, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a breakdown\", \"from\": 515, \"to\": 526}, {\"ngram\": \"a long line\", \"from\": 586, \"to\": 597}, {\"ngram\": \"spectacularly staged curtain raisers\", \"from\": 601, \"to\": 637}, {\"ngram\": \"the Summer Olympics\", \"from\": 641, \"to\": 660}, {\"ngram\": \"the first time\", \"from\": 666, \"to\": 680}, {\"ngram\": \"the event's history\", \"from\": 684, \"to\": 703}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 705, \"to\": 725}, {\"ngram\": \"an Olympic stadium\", \"from\": 752, \"to\": 770}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead, the Parisian spectacle will be staged on the city's main river, the Seine.\", \"from\": 773, \"to\": 856, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 850, \"end\": 855, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5497942034474478e-23, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Parisian spectacle\", \"from\": 782, \"to\": 804}, {\"ngram\": \"the city's main river\", \"from\": 823, \"to\": 844}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The nature of the opening ceremony and the precise details remain under wraps, but organisers have promised a show like no other and said it will be \\\"daring and joyful\\\".\", \"from\": 858, \"to\": 1027, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The nature\", \"from\": 858, \"to\": 868}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 872, \"to\": 892}, {\"ngram\": \"the precise details\", \"from\": 897, \"to\": 916}, {\"ngram\": \"wraps\", \"from\": 930, \"to\": 935}, {\"ngram\": \"organisers\", \"from\": 941, \"to\": 951}, {\"ngram\": \"a show\", \"from\": 966, \"to\": 972}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A secret that was impossible to keep was that the Paris Olympic Stadium would not be included in the opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 1029, \"to\": 1147, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A secret\", \"from\": 1029, \"to\": 1037}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympic Stadium\", \"from\": 1075, \"to\": 1100}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 1126, \"to\": 1146}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Spectators were told they would instead be required to line the banks of the Seine.\", \"from\": 1148, \"to\": 1231, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1225, \"end\": 1230, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5497942034474478e-23, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Spectators\", \"from\": 1148, \"to\": 1158}, {\"ngram\": \"the banks\", \"from\": 1208, \"to\": 1217}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dozens of boats will carry thousands of athletes and performers on a 6km (3.7-mile) floating parade by river through the heart of the French capital.\", \"from\": 1233, \"to\": 1382, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1367, \"end\": 1373, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.989547817742788, \"rank\": 0.010081156060865954, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Dozens\", \"from\": 1233, \"to\": 1239}, {\"ngram\": \"boats\", \"from\": 1243, \"to\": 1248}, {\"ngram\": \"thousands\", \"from\": 1260, \"to\": 1269}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 1273, \"to\": 1281}, {\"ngram\": \"performers\", \"from\": 1286, \"to\": 1296}, {\"ngram\": \"3.7-mile\", \"from\": 1307, \"to\": 1315}, {\"ngram\": \"river\", \"from\": 1336, \"to\": 1341}, {\"ngram\": \"the heart\", \"from\": 1350, \"to\": 1359}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The extravaganza will depart from the Austerlitz Bridge, sail by Notre-Dame de Paris Cathedral and arrive near the Eiffel Tower.\", \"from\": 1384, \"to\": 1512, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1422, \"end\": 1439, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_d'Austerlitz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Austerlitz Bridge\", \"types\": [\"Q12280\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_d'Austerlitz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_d'Austerlitz\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The extravaganza\", \"from\": 1384, \"to\": 1400}, {\"ngram\": \"sail\", \"from\": 1441, \"to\": 1445}, {\"ngram\": \"Notre-Dame de Paris Cathedral\", \"from\": 1449, \"to\": 1478}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 1495, \"to\": 1511}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Along the way, it will pass under bridges and gateways, including the Pont des Arts and Pont Neuf, while taking in many of the city's most famous landmarks.\", \"from\": 1514, \"to\": 1670, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1584, \"end\": 1597, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_des_Arts\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pont des Arts\", \"types\": [\"Q12280\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_des_Arts\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_des_Arts\"}, {\"begin\": 1602, \"end\": 1611, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_Neuf\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7832608629670382e-49, \"text\": \"Pont Neuf\", \"types\": [\"Q12280\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_Neuf\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_Neuf\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the way\", \"from\": 1520, \"to\": 1527}, {\"ngram\": \"bridges\", \"from\": 1548, \"to\": 1555}, {\"ngram\": \"gateways\", \"from\": 1560, \"to\": 1568}, {\"ngram\": \"the city's most famous landmarks\", \"from\": 1637, \"to\": 1669}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Organisers have promised \\\"there will not be a single riverbank or bridge that will not be filled with music, dance or performance\\\", adding that they will take advantage of the historic monuments, the riverbanks, the sky and water.\", \"from\": 1672, \"to\": 1902, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Organisers\", \"from\": 1672, \"to\": 1682}, {\"ngram\": \"a single riverbank\", \"from\": 1716, \"to\": 1734}, {\"ngram\": \"bridge\", \"from\": 1738, \"to\": 1744}, {\"ngram\": \"music\", \"from\": 1774, \"to\": 1779}, {\"ngram\": \"dance\", \"from\": 1781, \"to\": 1786}, {\"ngram\": \"performance\", \"from\": 1790, \"to\": 1801}, {\"ngram\": \"advantage\", \"from\": 1831, \"to\": 1840}, {\"ngram\": \"the historic monuments\", \"from\": 1844, \"to\": 1866}, {\"ngram\": \"the riverbanks\", \"from\": 1868, \"to\": 1882}, {\"ngram\": \"the sky\", \"from\": 1884, \"to\": 1891}, {\"ngram\": \"water\", \"from\": 1896, \"to\": 1901}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The artists who will perform throughout the event have been kept secret although the run time is expected to be four hours.\", \"from\": 1904, \"to\": 2027, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The artists\", \"from\": 1904, \"to\": 1915}, {\"ngram\": \"the event\", \"from\": 1944, \"to\": 1953}, {\"ngram\": \"the run time\", \"from\": 1985, \"to\": 1997}, {\"ngram\": \"four hours\", \"from\": 2016, \"to\": 2026}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There have been widespread media reports that famous performers like Celine Dion and Lady Gaga are involved in the opening ceremony - but these reports have not been confirmed by the organisers.\", \"from\": 2028, \"to\": 2222, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2097, \"end\": 2108, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.24104995353623e-37, \"text\": \"Celine Dion\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\"}, {\"begin\": 2113, \"end\": 2122, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lady Gaga\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"widespread media reports\", \"from\": 2044, \"to\": 2068}, {\"ngram\": \"famous performers\", \"from\": 2074, \"to\": 2091}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 2139, \"to\": 2159}, {\"ngram\": \"these reports\", \"from\": 2166, \"to\": 2179}, {\"ngram\": \"the organisers\", \"from\": 2207, \"to\": 2221}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thomas Jolly, the artistic director of the opening ceremony, painted the picture, however, by suggesting the show will be \\\"a large fresco\\\" celebrating Paris, France and the games and will interweave a parade of athletes, artistic performances and elements of protocol.\", \"from\": 2224, \"to\": 2492, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2224, \"end\": 2230, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"score\": 0.8057032465528977, \"rank\": 0.22162968089388688, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\"}, {\"begin\": 2375, \"end\": 2380, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4735882206370026e-22, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2382, \"end\": 2388, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999798760819784, \"rank\": 1.578445417473057e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the artistic director\", \"from\": 2238, \"to\": 2259}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 2263, \"to\": 2283}, {\"ngram\": \"the picture\", \"from\": 2293, \"to\": 2304}, {\"ngram\": \"the show\", \"from\": 2329, \"to\": 2337}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"a large fresco\", \"from\": 2346, \"to\": 2361}, {\"ngram\": \"the games\", \"from\": 2393, \"to\": 2402}, {\"ngram\": \"a parade\", \"from\": 2423, \"to\": 2431}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 2435, \"to\": 2443}, {\"ngram\": \"artistic performances\", \"from\": 2445, \"to\": 2466}, {\"ngram\": \"elements\", \"from\": 2471, \"to\": 2479}, {\"ngram\": \"protocol\", \"from\": 2483, \"to\": 2491}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sitting on the banks of the Seine will be more than 100 heads of state and government while more than 300,000 spectators are also expected to line the river.\", \"from\": 2494, \"to\": 2651, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2522, \"end\": 2527, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5497942034474478e-23, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the banks\", \"from\": 2505, \"to\": 2514}, {\"ngram\": \"more than 100 heads\", \"from\": 2536, \"to\": 2555}, {\"ngram\": \"state\", \"from\": 2559, \"to\": 2564}, {\"ngram\": \"government\", \"from\": 2569, \"to\": 2579}, {\"ngram\": \"more than 300,000 spectators\", \"from\": 2586, \"to\": 2614}, {\"ngram\": \"the river\", \"from\": 2641, \"to\": 2650}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Of those, 104,000 will have to buy tickets while it is estimated a further 222,000 will get free invitations.\", \"from\": 2652, \"to\": 2761, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"tickets\", \"from\": 2687, \"to\": 2694}, {\"ngram\": \"free invitations\", \"from\": 2744, \"to\": 2760}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That number does not include those who will find ways to access free vantage points along the way.\", \"from\": 2762, \"to\": 2860, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"That number\", \"from\": 2762, \"to\": 2773}, {\"ngram\": \"ways\", \"from\": 2811, \"to\": 2815}, {\"ngram\": \"free vantage points\", \"from\": 2826, \"to\": 2845}, {\"ngram\": \"the way\", \"from\": 2852, \"to\": 2859}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paris 2024 Organising Committee said about 10,500 athletes will take part in the opening ceremony and 80 giant screens along the route will offer intimate close-ups of the athletes and artists.\", \"from\": 2862, \"to\": 3059, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2866, \"end\": 2876, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.244774719137935e-15, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"about 10,500 athletes\", \"from\": 2903, \"to\": 2924}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 2935, \"to\": 2939}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 2943, \"to\": 2963}, {\"ngram\": \"80 giant screens\", \"from\": 2968, \"to\": 2984}, {\"ngram\": \"the route\", \"from\": 2991, \"to\": 3000}, {\"ngram\": \"intimate close-ups\", \"from\": 3012, \"to\": 3030}, {\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 3034, \"to\": 3046}, {\"ngram\": \"artists\", \"from\": 3051, \"to\": 3058}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Among one of the more high-profile flag bearer announcements this week, it was revealed on Monday that basketball iconLeBron Jameswill be one of the athletes to carry the flag for Team USA at the opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 3061, \"to\": 3274, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3096, \"end\": 3107, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Standard-bearer\", \"score\": 0.9999999999463398, \"rank\": 3.6756554517962417e-11, \"text\": \"flag bearer\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Standard-bearer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Standard-bearer\"}, {\"begin\": 3241, \"end\": 3249, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999999886313, \"rank\": 1.1293982241388624e-11, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Monday\", \"from\": 3152, \"to\": 3158}, {\"ngram\": \"iconLeBron\", \"from\": 3175, \"to\": 3185}, {\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 3206, \"to\": 3218}, {\"ngram\": \"the flag\", \"from\": 3228, \"to\": 3236}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 3253, \"to\": 3273}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The French have left nothing to chance when it comes to security for the opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 3276, \"to\": 3366, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3280, \"end\": 3286, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.989547817742788, \"rank\": 0